SIMPLE: counter-paly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Counter-paly
<hw>Coun"ter-pa`ly</hw> <pr>(-p?`l?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>contre-pal⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Paly, and
then divided fesswise, so that each vertical piece is cut into two,
having the colors used alternately or <xex>counterchanged</xex>. Thus
the escutcheon in the illustration may also be blazoned <xex>paly of six
per fess</xex> counterchanged <xex>argent and azure</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Counterpane</ent>⟦br⟧
